<Author>doggylover2
<Content>dog policy Guest beware of the dog policy of this company. While there is some flexibility as with size and age of pet there is a problem.Some city ordinences restrict breed of dogs allowed in city limits.We were not made aware of this until our 6th week of our extended stay.We have a large terrier mix older dog that looks like an American Pit Bull. This company does not take in to consideration that one bad apple doesnot spoil the whole bunch! We were told that we must get rid of our child because he looks like a pit bull! We were given one week to place him or move out.All in all our stay was not so bad but this one glich made our lives unbearable as we had to scramble to check out our options.This part of our stay was horrible. So if your dog is of questionable heritage please check the city ordinces and policys fully of any extend stay motel you choose.I hope this helps others not have a bad experience like we did.dog lover in dallas 
